// deploy/presets.custom.jsonc — OPTIONAL operator preset overlay.
//
// Copy this file to `deploy/presets.custom.jsonc` (gitignored) and edit it to
// override or add LLM presets WITHOUT editing the package. It is MERGED over
// the bundled catalogue (bp_router/llm/presets_catalog.jsonc) at first-boot
// seed:
//   - a custom entry whose `name` collides with a built-in WINS (replaces it),
//   - a new `name` is added.
//
// Consulted ONLY when seeding an empty `llm_presets` table (first boot, or
// after TRUNCATE llm_presets). After that, presets live in the DB and are
// admin-managed via /admin — editing this file does NOT retroactively change
// an already-seeded deployment.
//
// JSONC: `//` and `/* */` comments allowed; NO trailing commas. Each entry
// mirrors the `Preset` dataclass:
//   Required: name, provider, concrete_model, api_key_ref
//   Optional: description, min_user_level, default_temperature,
//             default_max_tokens, default_provider_options, api_key, base_url,
//             fallback_preset, max_retries
//   provider ∈ gemini | anthropic | openai | openai-embeddings |
//              openai-compatible | openai-compatible-embeddings
//   name must match ^[a-z][a-z0-9_-]{0,63}$ (lowercase, no dots).
//
// ── API KEYS: `api_key_ref` (preferred) vs `api_key` (inline) ──────────────
// A preset gets its provider credential one of two ways:
//
//   api_key_ref  — an INDIRECT reference resolved at call time. The only
//                  scheme wired out of the box is env://VAR, which reads the
//                  router container's environment. These vars already reach the
//                  container — just set their value in deploy/.env.prod:
//                    env://GEMINI_API_KEY, env://OPENAI_API_KEY,
//                    env://ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  (filled by scripts/prod.sh), and
//                    env://CUSTOM_LLM_API_KEY_1 .._2 .._3  (generic slots for
//                    custom/self-hosted providers — reference one here, set its
//                    value in deploy/.env.prod, done).
//                  Referencing some OTHER var name needs it added in TWO places:
//                  deploy/.env.prod AND the router service's `environment:`
//                  block in docker-compose.prod.yml (compose's --env-file only
//                  feeds ${...} interpolation, not the container) — so prefer a
//                  CUSTOM_LLM_API_KEY_* slot to skip the compose edit. A missing
//                  ref resolves to empty and calls 401. PREFERRED: only a
//                  reference lives in the DB/file.
//
//   api_key      — an INLINE literal secret. Takes precedence over api_key_ref
//                  when both are set. No env/compose edits — handy for a
//                  provider whose key isn't one of the three above, or a
//                  keyless local endpoint (use any dummy string). CAVEAT: it's
//                  stored PLAINTEXT in the llm_presets table (masked only on
//                  the admin API read-back, not at rest) and sits in plaintext
//                  in THIS file. Keep this file 0600 and off backups you don't
//                  trust. Avoid for shared/production secrets.
//
// Default below is an EMPTY array → a no-op overlay (safe to leave as-is).
// Example A — repoint `default` via an env ref (preferred):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "qwen3:32b",
//     "api_key_ref": "env://OPENAI_API_KEY",
//     "base_url": "http://ollama:11434/v1",
//     "description": "Local Qwen via Ollama — overrides the bundled default."
//   }
// Example B — non-standard provider via a generic key slot (preferred; set
//             CUSTOM_LLM_API_KEY_1 in deploy/.env.prod, no compose edit):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "deepseek-chat",
//     "api_key_ref": "env://CUSTOM_LLM_API_KEY_1",
//     "base_url": "https://api.deepseek.com/v1"
//   }
// Example C — same, but with an INLINE key (no env edit; plaintext in this file
//             + the DB — see the caveat above):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "deepseek-chat",
//     "api_key": "sk-...",
//     "base_url": "https://api.deepseek.com/v1"
//   }
[
]
